Description:
•	Production of seven (7) green book compliant business cases for housing site projects in year 1 of the BHF scheme (2020/21) that meet the requirements of TVCA's Assurance Framework, with potential for the extension of the commission for a further year (at TVCA's option;
•	Production and review of a comprehensive assessment matrix of the potential longlist of pipeline schemes to support the prioritisation for the BHF programme for years 2-5; 
•	Contribution to the development of a Programme Management framework to ensure we maximise return on current and any potential future funding allocations.

-	Develop future repair and maintenance liabilities forecast over the next 30 years;
-	Understand the Corporation's current position in relation to Decent Homes;
-	Create and model different standards of repairs from a 'cost floor' to 'aspirational standard' and understand the financial, technical and procurement issues surrounding them (particularly in light of recent government housing policy resulting in a 1% annual rent reduction up until 2019/20);
-	Have good information on the condition of block external and internal communal areas due to the high number of leaseholders in our housing stock;
-	Provide quality data to help inform our asset management strategy, business planning, asset performance modelling and investment planning tools
